					ovules 2 per locule;
					ovary in male flowers 0.7 by 1 mm, styles c. 0.3(-0.5) mm long.

Leaves with petiole 0.2-1.7(-2) cm and blade usually coriaceous, 1.7-11.5(-16.5) by 1-7(-8.5) cm, elliptic, oblong, ovate or obovate, with the base cuneate to truncate, rounded or rarely ± cordate and the apex usually rounded or obtuse, sometimes emarginate, rarely acute;
