Branching sometimes dichotomous;
					twigs sometimes slightly thickened or flattened at nodes;
					pale lenticels often prominent.

Leaves opposite and decussate or very rarely whorled (outside Malesia), simple, trifoliolate or imparipinnate, usually petiolate;
					petiole and rachis sometimes winged;
					lateral leaflets opposite, often asymmetrical at base, frequently smaller proximally in a given leaf;
