					filaments filiform;
					anthers broadly cordate, deeply incised at base and apiculate at apex.

Gynoecium of 2 (or 3) carpels fused at the level of ovary;
					ovary ovoid;
					locules 2 (or 3);
					styles 2 (or 3), free, subulate, glabrous, fur-rowed on adaxial side;
